Cell["\<\
On-shell Mandelstam kinematics and polarization products.

This block imposes massless four-point kinematics in terms of the Mandelstam \
variables s, t and u. The call to SetMandelstam sets p_i^2 = 0 and expresses \
scalar products of external momenta through s, t and u.

The convention is the all-momenta-incoming convention used by FeynCalc:
\tp1 + p2 + p3 + p4 = 0.
Thus the physical 2 -> 2 interpretation is obtained by the usual crossing \
convention for the outgoing particles.

The subsequent Pair[...] assignments specify the scalar products involving \
external polarization vectors. The variables h1, h2, h3 and h4 encode the \
helicity signs of the four external gravitons. The assumptions h_i^2 = 1 and \
s + t + u = 0 are imposed below.

If this notebook is meant to be fully standalone, consider clearing previous \
scalar-product definitions before this block, for example with \
FCClearScalarProducts[].\
\>", "Text",
 Editable->False,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.986288320932716*^9, 
  3.986288378234126*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ad2ffd1a-1254-4543-830b-\
8630eba00349"],

