Cell["\<\
Exchange-channel contributions.

The following three cells compute the s-, t- and u-channel contributions to \
the on-shell helicity amplitude. Each contribution is obtained by taking the \
generic exchange-channel tensor \[ScriptCapitalM]s, permuting the external \
legs appropriately, contracting it with the four external polarization \
tensors, and then simplifying the result using the Mandelstam relations.

The complex conjugation is applied to the polarization tensors associated \
with the outgoing external gravitons.\
\>", "Text",
 Editable->False,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.986288395514027*^9, 
  3.986288418211945*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"5ed783ff-da86-4ee1-9e9f-\
21d8986616d9"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"AmplitudeSChannel", "=", 
    RowBox[{"TrickMandelstam", "[", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"Simplify", "[", 
       RowBox[{"ScalarProductExpand", "[", 
        RowBox[{"FeynGravContractor", "[", 
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{"\[ScriptCapitalM]s", "[", 
           RowBox[{
           "\[Mu]1", ",", "\[Nu]1", ",", "\[Mu]2", ",", "\[Nu]2", ",", 
            "\[Mu]3", ",", "\[Nu]3", ",", "\[Mu]4", ",", "\[Nu]4", ",", "p1", 
            ",", "p2", ",", "p3", ",", "p4"}], "]"}], 
          RowBox[{"PolarizationTensor", "[", 
           RowBox[{"\[Mu]1", ",", "\[Nu]1", ",", "p1"}], "]"}], 
          RowBox[{"PolarizationTensor", "[", 
           RowBox[{"\[Mu]2", ",", "\[Nu]2", ",", "p2"}], "]"}], 
          RowBox[{"ComplexConjugate", "[", 
           RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"PolarizationTensor", "[", 
             RowBox[{"\[Mu]3", ",", "\[Nu]3", ",", "p3"}], "]"}], 
            RowBox[{"PolarizationTensor", "[", 
