Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Step 3.",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " Chunked contraction of the remaining tensor expression.\n\nBefore \
performing the final contraction, we inspect the sizes of the two remaining \
intermediate expressions. At this stage Part4 and Part3 are both expanded \
sums. Therefore Length[Part4] and Length[Part3] count their top-level \
additive terms.\n\nThe product Length[Part3] Length[Part4] gives a rough \
estimate of the number of pairwise products that would appear if the product \
Part4 Part3 were expanded before contraction. This is not the final number of \
terms in the contracted expression, because many terms can combine, simplify, \
or vanish during the tensor contraction. It is nevertheless a useful \
diagnostic for the size of the symbolic task."
}], "Text",
 Editable->False,
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.986354396549531*^9},ExpressionUUID->"6f2e3cb8-b943-4274-94d5-\
c270ef4207eb"],

