Cell["\<\
Optional checkpoint.

The final expression stored in theOutput is expensive to recompute. We \
therefore save it to disk in the same directory as this notebook.

The checkpoint is written in WXF format, the Wolfram Exchange Format. This is \
a binary format for serializing Wolfram Language expressions and is more \
suitable here than an MX dump file, because WXF is intended as a \
platform-independent exchange format.

A different notebook can load the expression with Import[..., \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]WXF\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]] and assign it to any \
variable name. This avoids rerunning the tensor contraction.\
\>", "Text",
 Editable->False,
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.986354734612186*^9},ExpressionUUID->"0b5538e2-4bea-49a9-bee6-\
031e8b3f7427"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Export", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"FileNameJoin", "[", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"NotebookDirectory", "[", "]"}], ",", 
       "\"\<Test5TriangleNumerator.wxf\>\""}], "}"}], "]"}], ",", "theOutput",
     ",", "\"\<WXF\>\""}], "]"}], ";"}]], "Input",
 Editable->False,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.986354752698913*^9, 3.986354775891638*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[23]:=",ExpressionUUID->"c6174674-fe6f-43a0-a57e-572447bd7e5c"],

